name: r-nmf
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.21.0' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-nmf
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  fn: NMF_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/NMF_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/NMF/NMF_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 3b30c81c66066fab4a63c5611a0313418b840d8b63414db31ef0e932872d02e3

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1004
  skip: true  # [win32]
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}        # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}      # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_cxx') }}        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}make
    - {{ posix }}sed               # [win]
    - {{ posix }}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-rcolorbrewer
    - r-cluster
    - r-colorspace
    - r-digest
    - r-doparallel
    - r-foreach
    - r-ggplot2
    - r-gridbase
    - r-pkgmaker >=0.20
    - r-registry
    - r-reshape2
    - r-rngtools >=1.2.3
    - r-stringr >=1.0.0
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{ native }}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-rcolorbrewer
    - r-cluster
    - r-colorspace
    - r-digest
    - r-doparallel
    - r-foreach
    - r-ggplot2
    - r-gridbase
    - r-pkgmaker >=0.20
    - r-registry
    - r-reshape2
    - r-rngtools >=1.2.3
    - r-stringr >=1.0.0

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('NMF')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('NMF')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: http://renozao.github.io/NMF
  license: GPL (>= 2)
  summary: Provides a framework to perform Non-negative Matrix Factorization (NMF). The package
    implements a set of already published algorithms and seeding methods, and provides
    a framework to test, develop and plug new/custom algorithms. Most of the built-in
    algorithms have been optimized in C++, and the main interface function provides
    an easy way of performing parallel computations on multicore machines.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
